HEADWORD: Riprap
<hw>Rip"rap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Rap</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Masonry)</fld> <def>A foundation or
sustaining wall of stones thrown together without order, as in deep
water or on a soft bottom, or in a river channel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riprap</ent>⟦br⟧

